      <h2>AP Music Theory</h2><article>
    <h3>1. Fundamentals of Music Notation</h3>
    <p>Staff, clefs (treble, bass, alto, tenor)...</p>
    <p>Note values, rests, ties, dots...</p>
    <p>Time signatures (simple, compound, irregular)...</p>
    <p>Key signatures and circle of fifths...</p>
    <p>Accidentals and enharmonic equivalents...</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>2. Scales and Modes</h3>
    <p>Major, minor (natural, harmonic, melodic)...</p>
    <p>Chromatic, whole tone scales, and church modes (Dorian, Phrygian, etc.)...</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>3. Intervals</h3>
    <p>Naming and identifying intervals (simple vs compound, inversion)...</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>4. Chords and Harmony</h3>
    <p>Triads, seventh chords, Roman numeral analysis, figured bass, lead sheet symbols...</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>5. Voice Leading and Part Writing</h3>
    <p>SATB part writing rules, chord inversions, resolution of dissonances, avoiding parallels...</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>6. Harmonic Progressions</h3>
    <p>Cadences, common progressions (ii-V-I), non-chord tones (suspension, passing, etc.)...</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>7. Form and Analysis</h3>
    <p>Binary, ternary, sonata, rondo, motivic development, sequences, phrase structure...</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>8. Aural Skills</h3>
    <p>Ear training: interval and chord recognition, dictation, sight singing...</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>9. Composition and Realization</h3>
    <p>Realizing figured bass, short compositions with harmonic guidelines...</p>
  </article>
